For Task-1, I created an infographic on the topic Digital Literacy for College Students. The aim of this infographic is to show the importance of digital literacy and how it helps students in their academic and professional life. Digital literacy means having the knowledge and skills to use digital technology like the internet, online platforms and software tools in a safe and effective way.
In the infographic, I explained the meaning of digital literacy and how it includes searching information online, communicating through digital platforms and using digital tools responsibly. I also mentioned some useful tools like Google Drive for file storage, GitHub for managing coding projects, LinkedIn for professional networking, Canva for designing and HackerRank for coding practice. These platforms help students improve their technical knowledge and productivity.
Another important part of the infographic is about online safety. I included some basic cyber safety practices such as using strong passwords, avoiding suspicious links, not sharing OTPs and enabling two-factor authentication. These practices are very important to protect personal data and prevent cyber fraud.
Through this infographic, I learned that digital literacy is an essential skill for every student because it helps us learn better, stay safe online and build a professional digital identity.
